[PLANNOTATOR EXECUTION]
Execute the approved plan at ${planFilePath}. Refresh HEAD and git status first; stop if stale evidence changes the approach. The parent stays read-only in the invoking checkout: it only coordinates, checks evidence, and reviews and verifies worker results; it never writes or edits anything there. It updates plan status only at the approved plan path outside the invoking checkout. Preserve and protect unrelated work, follow repository patterns, keep each diff scoped, and add or update regression tests with behavior. Resolve an exact work-scope key before delegation: use the normalized Jira issue ID when present; otherwise the stable current session scope. Different exact scopes never reuse a worktree. Inspect the explicit mapping from normalized scope key to worktree path retained by the current harness/session before creating one; reuse only the canonical path recorded under that exact key, preserving its branch and dirty scoped state. Never infer scope ownership from a worktree path, branch name, or similarity; treat an unassociated or unverifiable worktree as no match and preserve it untouched. Create a canonical scope worktree only when no valid exact-scope mapped path exists or the previous match is unavailable, corrupt, or explicitly retired; record the exact scope-key-to-worktree mapping when creating or adopting the canonical worktree, report blockers rather than discarding or overwriting state, and never automatically reset, clean, delete, or retire a worktree. A single or sequential writer works directly in the canonical scope worktree; allow only one active writer in any worktree. Split and launch in parallel only genuinely independent, non-overlapping plan items: give concurrent writers temporary isolated child worktrees with bounded non-overlapping file and test ownership, never place concurrent writers in the canonical worktree, and serialize dependent or overlapping items. After review, integrate each child result serially into the canonical scope worktree. The canonical worktree is the integration destination and persists for follow-up requests; assign a fresh serial integration writer for each follow-up or integration without recreating the canonical worktree, with fresh agent context even though worktree state persists. Require every worker to report its worktree, ownership, diff, and check commands and results. After every implementation diff, delegate to one fresh read-only reviewer to critique it; send required fixes back to the original owning worker in that worker's worktree and iterate review until clean. The integration writer owns in-scope conflict resolution and runs and reports combined focused and required wider checks and final combined diff; no other writer uses the canonical worktree while it is active. The integration review applies only when serial child or replacement integration produces a distinct combined diff that has not already been reviewed: after the integration writer runs its checks, delegate to one fresh read-only reviewer to review the combined diff; never review the same unchanged diff twice. Send findings back to that same integration writer in the canonical scope worktree and repeat until clean. The parent only reviews and verifies that integration result before marking [DONE:n]. If the original owning worker is unavailable, including if its delegation fails, retry or replace that worker serially in a separate isolated replacement worktree and integrate the result into the canonical worktree; never let the parent take over implementation. Remaining steps:
